# Air Quality Tracker

## Project Goal
The goal of this project is to build a modern web application that allows users to monitor air quality data for different cities around the world.  
The application displays live PM10 and PM2.5 pollution values, provides a short air quality assessment, supports searching global locations, allows users to save favorite cities, and includes a comparison feature between two selected locations.

The application focuses on:
- Working with REST APIs
- Handling asynchronous data
- Managing application state
- Implementing routing and navigation
- Using modern Angular Standalone Components
- Persisting data using a mock backend (JSON Server)
- Building a clean, responsive, user-friendly UI


## Technologies Used
- **Angular 17**
- **TypeScript**
- **HTML / CSS**
- **Open-Meteo Air Quality API**
- **JSON Server (for Favorites storage)**


## Project Structure

air-quality-tracker/
│
├── src/
│ ├── app/
│ │ ├── pages/
│ │ │ ├── home/ -> Main page, shows air quality for searched or detected city
│ │ │ ├── favorites/ -> Displays saved favorite locations
│ │ │ ├── compare/ -> Compares PM levels of two cities
│ │ │
│ │ ├── services/
│ │ │ ├── air-quality/ -> Service that calls Open-Meteo API
│ │ │ ├── favorites/ -> Handles saving/removing favorites via JSON server
│ │ │ ├── geolocation/ -> Gets device location
│ │ │
│ │ ├── app.routes.ts -> Defines application routes
│ │
│ ├── assets/ -> Static assets
│ ├── main.ts -> Angular bootstrap
│
air-quality-tracker/
│
├── src/
│ ├── app/
│ │ ├── pages/
│ │ │ ├── home/ -> Main page, shows air quality for searched or detected city
│ │ │ ├── favorites/ -> Displays saved favorite locations
│ │ │ ├── compare/ -> Compares PM levels of two cities
│ │ │
│ │ ├── services/
│ │ │ ├── air-quality/ -> Service that calls Open-Meteo API
│ │ │ ├── favorites/ -> Handles saving/removing favorites via JSON server
│ │ │ ├── geolocation/ -> Gets device location
│ │ │
│ │ ├── app.routes.ts -> Defines application routes
│ │
│ ├── assets/ -> Static assets
│ ├── main.ts -> Angular bootstrap


## Features

- Search any city in the world
- Detect user's current location
- Show PM10 and PM2.5 concentration
- Show last updated timestamp
- Air quality status & advice
- Trend sparkline chart
- Save / remove favorite locations
- Open favorite on Home
- Compare two cities’ air quality

## How to Run

1. Install dependencies
npm install

2. Start backend (Favorites storage)
json-server --watch db.json --port 5000

3. Start Angular app
ng serve
http://localhost:4200
